 1970s and 1980s. Taken as a whole, the collection demonstrates the extent to which the far left has weaved its influence into the political fabric of Britain.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRight and left (Political science)zGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocialismzGreat Britainy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Communism, Post-Communism & Socialism.2bisacsh  aBritish history.  aBritish politics.  aBritish society.  aLabour Party.  aSocialist Party.  aSocialist Workers Party.  aTrotskyism.  aanarchism.  aanti-colonialism.  aanti-fascism.  aanti-racism.  aanti-revisionism.  aeconomic crisis.  agay liberation.  alabour movement.  asocial issues.  asocial movements.1 aBirchall, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlackledge, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruley, Sue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurton-Cartledge, Phil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCallaghan, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCross, Rich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHayes, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHughes, Celia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParker, Lawrence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPearmain, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRenton, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Evan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Evan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVirdee, Satnam